    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-01T07:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-01T07:44:00-05:00" n="499"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-01T12:00:00-00:44"
                            >May 1, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Department’s 102, April 30, 1 p.m. According to President Barclay, British
                    have not approached him in this matter. He informs me that if British request
                    permission of his Government for this operation of 11 planes he will act
                    favorably thereon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
